args: (Hot bowl'a oatmeal! Can't believe I went\nand found a suspicious sort so darn quick!\nThis here's even better'n I'd hoped...)
Whoops! Sorry, I was in a hur... Wait,\nLady Mitsuhide?! THE Lady Mitsuhide?!
Oh, right. You work for Seimei.\nIt's, er, Kuzunoha or...something?
Aw, horse nuggets! We gotta hide!
Come out! I know you're there!
I heard rumors Seimei was in this area—\nI assume the two of you are also trying\nto chase down the Mukuroshu?
Huh? He didn't, like, order you to do it?
(C'mon. There's no WAY he'd leave a\nmission like this to an idiot like her!)
Mind if we hoof it while we talk? I can't\nlose sight'a them Mukuroshu types if'n\nI wanna get revenge on Lord Seimei.
Uh, sure, all right. Lead the way.\n(She is SO gonna screw this up...)

...So basically you want to find who's
responsible for these disappearances
so you can make Seimei feel bad for
saying terrible things about you?
That's it, all right! What about yerself?
I'm after the same thing—er, though not\nexactly for the same reason. I just want to\nbring peace back to the land, y'know?

Anyway, that's why I've been walking
around keeping my eyes peeled for anyone
suspicious. Only seems right, what with
this being part of my territory and all.
Hoo-eee! And here I heard ya didn't have\ntime for nothin' but slackin' off!
Hard to slack off when the world is on fire.
Plus everybody else who could do\nsomething is out on even bigger threats.
Don't worry your fuzzy head about it.\nHow about we just work together here\nsince we're after the same thing?
Unlike Seimei, no one's ordered me to\nlook into the Mukuroshu—I just hate\n'em stirring up trouble in my territory.
Wait, what? Why? Two people can solve\nthis thing twice as fast, right?
Yer head of a Wyrmclan just like Lord\nSeimei, which means yer his rival what\nto be the next shogun.
And you think I'm going to try and steal\nall the glory to help me with that?
I'll tell you a secret, fox: I couldn't give\none whit about that stupid job.
Ain't about what YOU think—\nit's about what Lord Seimei thinks.
Ah, and you think he'll hate knowing that\nI helped him with a problem he sees as\nhis own? ...Yeah, okay. That's fair.
Yep! Ya hit that mouse right on the noggin'!\nEr, hope that don't offend ya none.
Plus, I can't be showin' him how wrong he\nis 'bout my talent and usefulness if'n\nI get help from every darn passin' hand!
If I don't do this all on m'lonesome,\nhe ain't never gonna ask me to stay.
No, that all makes sense—but can you\nREALLY do this by yourself?
Just that you're clearly not cut out for...\nYou know what? This isn't my business.\nGood luck byeeeeee!
Oof. She really knows how to hit a fox\nright in the ol' snout...
Not a secret I ain't cut out for this\nwhole ＂trailin' folk＂ business.
But I wanna be useful—and if I can do\nsomethin' good on m'own, Lord Seimei's\nsure to praise me heaps!
Which means I gotta hop back on the\nmule and find the Mukuroshu's trail!
Can't believe they made a base inside a\ncave like this. Better take me a gander...
(Sweet potato pie! That's gotta be one'a\nthe folks what went and got kidnapped!\nI KNEW the Mukuroshu was behind this!)
Tsk! Just the wind. I really gotta find\na more low-key line of work...
Whew! That was close. But it's sure as\nheck good to see ya, Lady Mitsuhide!\nHow long ya been here?
Oh, for quite a while now. But since you\nmade it PERFECTLY clear that you wanted\nto work alone, I tried to stay hidden.
Well then, I owe ya twice over for savin'\nme. Thought I was gonna be pushin'\nup pretty flowers there for a tick.
Think nothing of it. If you'd been found,\nmy hard work would've been for nothing.
Still, it means I didn't find the darn\nMukuroshu base on m'own after all.
Sure you did! I just got here first.
That's a real bum steer of a prize there...
Anyway, I'd hurry back to Seimei and fill\nhim in on all of this if I were you.
The Mukuroshu don't stay in one place\nfor very long, you know?
And if you don't hurry, this hideout's gonna\nbe empty before he can even get here.
I appreciate the warnin', but I can take 'er\nfrom here. Lord Seimei's gonna have these\nfolks handled a'fore ya can say 'boo'!
So I can just sit around and watch\nall the fun? Perfect.
We need to find our next abduction victim\nand start... Huh? What's that?
...A jufu? Heh. Looks like we've got\nSeimei's little shikigami on our tails.
Better let Master Doman know about this.\nHeh heh... Bring it on, Seimei!
